title: Native Instruments Traktor Pro 2 v2.6.8 Incl. Patch-Tracer [deep
description:
Native Instruments Traktor Pro 2 v2.6.8








             ELEVATE YOUR MIX - Define your sound with our flagship DJ software four decks and a stunning range of creative features for maximum freedom in mixing. TRAKTOR is the pro platform that top DJs trust, and TRAKTOR PRO 2 with Remix Deck technology is the most advanced version of TRAKTOR ever. Perform your mix on up to four decks, featuring TruWave colored waveforms, powerful looping and cueing functionality and an exceptional effects suite. TRAKTOR PRO 2 is Ready to Remix. Get started in seconds, fire up the Remix Decks and seamlessly merge the worlds of DJing and live performance.

TruWave colored waveform displays on all 4 decks
Remix Decks, Loop Recorder, Macro FX and more
Customizable mappings for all relevant DJ controllers




       ============================
       What's New in TRAKTOR 2.6.8
       ============================
         

         - New Controller Editor 1.6.2.1863 now allows full MIDI mapping of
KONTROL Z1, S2 MK2, S4 MK2 and X1 MK2

- This update fixes a crash caused by m4a files which contain cover art and were edited in version 2.6.6


                      SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

        Windows 7 or 8 (latest Service Pack, 32/64 Bit), 2.0 GHz Intel Core 2 Duo or AMD Athlon 64 X2, 2 GB RAM (4 GB recommended)


General: Monitor with 1024 x 768 screen resolution, USB 2.0, 1 GB free disc space, high-speed internet required



                       SUPPORTED DRIVERS

   ASIO
   Core Audio
   DirectSound
   WASAPI



                     SUPPORTED AUDIO FORMATS

MP3, WAV, AIFF, Audio-CD, FLAC, Ogg Vorbis, non-DRM WMA (Windows only), non-DRM AAC









                         INSTALLATION:

     

     Next open the .rar file by double clicking it. If you can't open it you need to get an archiver which supports rar files such as Winrar and extract.



              Install Traktor Pro.
                                             
              Copyapply a Patch (the one you need) in the Install-Dir.
